code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_resume"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The azx_resume() function is missing a synchronize_irq() call after acquiring the IRQ. When the device resumes from suspend, the IRQ state may have pending interrupts from before the sleep. Without synchronize_irq() to flush these pending IRQs, the IRQ handler can't properly communicate with the codec, causing azx_get_response() to timeout. This triggers the exact error sequence reported: switching to polling mode, disabling MSI, and switching to single_cmd mode. The probe function (lines 3155-3159) correctly includes synchronize_irq() after azx_acquire_irq(), but the resume function (line 2557) is missing this critical synchronization step."
}

